{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":539,"text":"I know this is going to sound strange,"},{"time":3382,"text":"but I think robots can inspire us\nto be better humans."},{"time":9245,"text":"See, I grew up in Bethlehem, Pennsylvania,"},{"time":12363,"text":"the home of Bethlehem Steel."},{"time":14991,"text":"My father was an engineer,"},{"time":17127,"text":"and when I was growing up,\nhe would teach me how things worked."},{"time":21470,"text":"We would build projects together,"},{"time":23588,"text":"like model rockets and slot cars."},{"time":26732,"text":"Here's the go-kart that we built together."},{"time":30208,"text":"That's me behind the wheel,"},{"time":31976,"text":"with my sister and my best\nfriend at the time."},{"time":35875,"text":"And one day,"},{"time":37825,"text":"he came home, when I was\nabout 10 years old,"},{"time":40932,"text":"and at the dinner table, he announced"},{"time":43582,"text":"that for our next project, \nwe were going to build ..."},{"time":47318,"text":"a robot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49604,"text":"A robot."},{"time":51120,"text":"Now, I was thrilled about this,"},{"time":53207,"text":"because at school,\nthere was a bully named Kevin,"},{"time":57033,"text":"and he was picking on me,"},{"time":58946,"text":"because I was the only\nJewish kid in class."},{"time":61910,"text":"So I couldn't wait to get\nstarted to work on this,"},{"time":64307,"text":"so I could introduce Kevin to my robot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66941,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":67995,"text":"(Robot noises)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":77552,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":78968,"text":"But that wasn't the kind of robot\nmy dad had in mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82841,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":83933,"text":"See, he owned a chromium-plating company,"},{"time":87589,"text":"and they had to move heavy steel parts\nbetween tanks of chemicals."},{"time":93486,"text":"And so he needed\nan industrial robot like this,"},{"time":96883,"text":"that could basically do the heavy lifting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99684,"text":"But my dad didn't get\nthe kind of robot he wanted, either."},{"time":103870,"text":"He and I worked on it for several years,"},{"time":106324,"text":"but it was the 1970s, and the technology\nthat was available to amateurs"},{"time":111093,"text":"just wasn't there yet."},{"time":113992,"text":"So Dad continued to do\nthis kind of work by hand."},{"time":117595,"text":"And a few years later,"},{"time":119730,"text":"he was diagnosed with cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123822,"text":"You see,"},{"time":125416,"text":"what the robot we were trying\nto build was telling him"},{"time":128036,"text":"was not about doing the heavy lifting."},{"time":130216,"text":"It was a warning"},{"time":131391,"text":"about his exposure to the toxic chemicals."},{"time":135184,"text":"He didn't recognize that at the time,"},{"time":137501,"text":"and he contracted leukemia."},{"time":139827,"text":"And he died at the age of 45."},{"time":143354,"text":"I was devastated by this."},{"time":145703,"text":"And I never forgot the robot\nthat he and I tried to build."},{"time":150195,"text":"When I was at college, I decided\nto study engineering, like him."},{"time":155081,"text":"And I went to Carnegie Mellon,\nand I earned my PhD in robotics."},{"time":159653,"text":"I've been studying robots ever since."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162721,"text":"So what I'd like to tell you about\nare four robot projects,"},{"time":167340,"text":"and how they've inspired me\nto be a better human."},{"time":174206,"text":"By 1993, I was a young professor at USC,"},{"time":179844,"text":"and I was just building up\nmy own robotics lab,"},{"time":182686,"text":"and this was the year\nthe World Wide Web came out."},{"time":186487,"text":"And I remember my students\nwere the ones who told me about it,"},{"time":189496,"text":"and we would -- we were just amazed."},{"time":191837,"text":"We started playing with this,\nand that afternoon,"},{"time":195244,"text":"we realized that we could use\nthis new, universal interface"},{"time":199546,"text":"to allow anyone in the world\nto operate the robot in our lab."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205339,"text":"So, rather than have it fight\nor do industrial work,"},{"time":210413,"text":"we decided to build a planter,"},{"time":212967,"text":"put the robot into the center of it,"},{"time":214942,"text":"and we called it the Telegarden."},{"time":217736,"text":"And we had put a camera\nin the gripper of the hand of the robot,"},{"time":222277,"text":"and we wrote some\nspecial scripts and software,"},{"time":225232,"text":"so that anyone in the world could come in,"},{"time":227290,"text":"and by clicking on the screen,"},{"time":229098,"text":"they could move the robot around\nand visit the garden."},{"time":233416,"text":"But we also set up some other software"},{"time":237291,"text":"that lets you participate\nand help us water the garden, remotely."},{"time":241643,"text":"And if you watered it a few times,"},{"time":243956,"text":"we'd give you your own seed to plant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247167,"text":"Now, this was an engineering project,"},{"time":250667,"text":"and we published some papers\non the system design of it,"},{"time":254803,"text":"but we also thought of it\nas an art installation."},{"time":258638,"text":"It was invited, after the first year,"},{"time":260811,"text":"by the Ars Electronica Museum in Austria,"},{"time":263855,"text":"to have it installed in their lobby."},{"time":267558,"text":"And I'm happy to say, it remained\nonline there, 24 hours a day,"},{"time":271569,"text":"for almost nine years."},{"time":274369,"text":"That robot was operated by more people"},{"time":278168,"text":"than any other robot in history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281303,"text":"Now, one day,"},{"time":282954,"text":"I got a call out of the blue\nfrom a student,"},{"time":287211,"text":"who asked a very simple\nbut profound question."},{"time":292361,"text":"He said, \"Is the robot real?\""},{"time":296599,"text":"Now, everyone else had assumed it was,"},{"time":298909,"text":"and we knew it was,\nbecause we were working with it."},{"time":301449,"text":"But I knew what he meant,"},{"time":302871,"text":"because it would be possible"},{"time":304337,"text":"to take a bunch of pictures\nof flowers in a garden"},{"time":307146,"text":"and then, basically, index them\nin a computer system,"},{"time":310809,"text":"such that it would appear\nthat there was a real robot,"},{"time":313460,"text":"when there wasn't."},{"time":315088,"text":"And the more I thought about it,"},{"time":316636,"text":"I couldn't think of a good answer\nfor how he could tell the difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320628,"text":"This was right about the time\nthat I was offered a position"},{"time":323449,"text":"here at Berkeley."},{"time":324774,"text":"And when I got here,"},{"time":326443,"text":"I looked up Hubert Dreyfus,"},{"time":328829,"text":"who's a world-renowned\nprofessor of philosophy,"},{"time":332582,"text":"And I talked with him\nabout this and he said,"},{"time":335336,"text":"\"This is one of the oldest\nand most central problems in philosophy."},{"time":339462,"text":"It goes back to the Skeptics\nand up through Descartes."},{"time":343503,"text":"It's the issue of epistemology,"},{"time":346709,"text":"the study of how do we know\nthat something is true.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":350625,"text":"So he and I started working together,"},{"time":352649,"text":"and we coined a new term:\n\"telepistemology,\""},{"time":356757,"text":"the study of knowledge at a distance."},{"time":359303,"text":"We invited leading artists,\nengineers and philosophers"},{"time":363818,"text":"to write essays about this,"},{"time":365161,"text":"and the results are collected\nin this book from MIT Press."},{"time":369959,"text":"So thanks to this student,"},{"time":372079,"text":"who questioned what everyone else\nhad assumed to be true,"},{"time":375422,"text":"this project taught me\nan important lesson about life,"},{"time":379423,"text":"which is to always question assumptions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383807,"text":"Now, the second project\nI'll tell you about"},{"time":386007,"text":"grew out of the Telegarden."},{"time":388023,"text":"As it was operating, my students\nand I were very interested"},{"time":390868,"text":"in how people were interacting\nwith each other,"},{"time":393233,"text":"and what they were doing with the garden."},{"time":395314,"text":"So we started thinking:"},{"time":396489,"text":"what if the robot could leave the garden"},{"time":398481,"text":"and go out into some other\ninteresting environment?"},{"time":401319,"text":"Like, for example,\nwhat if it could go to a dinner party"},{"time":404084,"text":"at the White House?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":405569,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":408401,"text":"So, because we were interested\nmore in the system design"},{"time":411994,"text":"and the user interface\nthan in the hardware,"},{"time":414961,"text":"we decided that,"},{"time":416136,"text":"rather than have a robot replace\nthe human to go to the party,"},{"time":420647,"text":"we'd have a human replace the robot."},{"time":423679,"text":"We called it the Tele-Actor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425978,"text":"We got a human,"},{"time":428010,"text":"someone who's very\noutgoing and gregarious,"},{"time":431142,"text":"and she was outfitted with a helmet\nwith various equipment,"},{"time":435421,"text":"cameras and microphones,"},{"time":436729,"text":"and then a backpack with wireless\nInternet connection."},{"time":440882,"text":"And the idea was that she could go"},{"time":443050,"text":"into a remote and interesting environment,"},{"time":445524,"text":"and then over the Internet,"},{"time":447565,"text":"people could experience\nwhat she was experiencing."},{"time":450736,"text":"So they could see what she was seeing,"},{"time":453731,"text":"but then, more importantly,\nthey could participate,"},{"time":457038,"text":"by interacting with each other\nand coming up with ideas"},{"time":461812,"text":"about what she should do next\nand where she should go,"},{"time":465805,"text":"and then conveying those\nto the Tele-Actor."},{"time":469069,"text":"So we got a chance to take the Tele-Actor"},{"time":471514,"text":"to the Webby Awards in San Francisco."},{"time":475129,"text":"And that year, Sam Donaldson was the host."},{"time":480290,"text":"Just before the curtain went\nup, I had about 30 seconds"},{"time":483004,"text":"to explain to Mr. Donaldson\nwhat we were going to do."},{"time":488119,"text":"And I said, \"The Tele-Actor\nis going to be joining you onstage."},{"time":491660,"text":"This is a new experimental project,"},{"time":494038,"text":"and people are watching her\non their screens,"},{"time":496657,"text":"there's cameras involved\nand there's microphones"},{"time":499972,"text":"and she's got an earbud in her ear,"},{"time":501782,"text":"and people over the network\nare giving her advice"},{"time":504123,"text":"about what to do next.\""},{"time":505305,"text":"And he said, \"Wait a second."},{"time":507806,"text":"That's what I do.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":509003,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":514004,"text":"So he loved the concept,"},{"time":515900,"text":"and when the Tele-Actor walked onstage,\nshe walked right up to him,"},{"time":520177,"text":"and she gave him a big kiss\nright on the lips."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522660,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":524636,"text":"We were totally surprised --\nwe had no idea that would happen."},{"time":527582,"text":"And he was great, he just gave her\na big hug in return,"},{"time":530224,"text":"and it worked out great."},{"time":531905,"text":"But that night, as we were packing up,"},{"time":533969,"text":"I asked the Tele-Actor,\nhow did the Tele-Directors decide"},{"time":538548,"text":"that they would give\na kiss to Sam Donaldson?"},{"time":543135,"text":"And she said they hadn't."},{"time":545274,"text":"She said, when she was\njust about to walk onstage,"},{"time":547916,"text":"the Tele-Directors still were trying\nto agree on what to do,"},{"time":550914,"text":"and so she just walked onstage\nand did what felt most natural."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554038,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":558576,"text":"So, the success\nof the Tele-Actor that night"},{"time":561692,"text":"was due to the fact\nthat she was a wonderful actor."},{"time":565969,"text":"She knew when to trust her instincts."},{"time":568422,"text":"And so that project taught me\nanother lesson about life,"},{"time":572375,"text":"which is that, when in doubt, improvise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576046,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":578664,"text":"Now, the third project\ngrew out of my experience"},{"time":583607,"text":"when my father was in the hospital."},{"time":587284,"text":"He was undergoing a treatment --\nchemotherapy treatments --"},{"time":590661,"text":"and there's a related treatment\ncalled brachytherapy,"},{"time":594955,"text":"where tiny, radioactive seeds\nare placed into the body"},{"time":598767,"text":"to treat cancerous tumors."},{"time":601572,"text":"And the way it's done,\nas you can see here,"},{"time":603867,"text":"is that surgeons\ninsert needles into the body"},{"time":608258,"text":"to deliver the seeds."},{"time":609974,"text":"And all these needles\nare inserted in parallel."},{"time":614445,"text":"So it's very common that some\nof the needles penetrate sensitive organs."},{"time":620635,"text":"And as a result, the needles damage\nthese organs, cause damage,"},{"time":627632,"text":"which leads to trauma and side effects."},{"time":630581,"text":"So my students and I wondered:"},{"time":632249,"text":"what if we could modify the system,"},{"time":636795,"text":"so that the needles\ncould come in at different angles?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":640395,"text":"So we simulated this;"},{"time":642262,"text":"we developed some optimization\nalgorithms and we simulated this."},{"time":645731,"text":"And we were able to show"},{"time":646906,"text":"that we are able to avoid\nthe delicate organs,"},{"time":649492,"text":"and yet still achieve the coverage\nof the tumors with the radiation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655313,"text":"So now, we're working with doctors at UCSF"},{"time":658811,"text":"and engineers at Johns Hopkins,"},{"time":661102,"text":"and we're building a robot\nthat has a number of --"},{"time":665088,"text":"it's a specialized design\nwith different joints"},{"time":667711,"text":"that can allow the needles to come in\nat an infinite variety of angles."},{"time":672483,"text":"And as you can see here,\nthey can avoid delicate organs"},{"time":676229,"text":"and still reach the targets\nthey're aiming for."},{"time":680019,"text":"So, by questioning this assumption\nthat all the needles have to be parallel,"},{"time":685028,"text":"this project also taught me\nan important lesson:"},{"time":688114,"text":"When in doubt, when your path\nis blocked, pivot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693797,"text":"And the last project\nalso has to do with medical robotics."},{"time":698187,"text":"And this is something\nthat's grown out of a system"},{"time":701781,"text":"called the da Vinci surgical robot."},{"time":705866,"text":"And this is a commercially\navailable device."},{"time":708334,"text":"It's being used in over 2,000\nhospitals around the world."},{"time":712013,"text":"The idea is it allows the surgeon\nto operate comfortably"},{"time":716410,"text":"in his own coordinate frame."},{"time":720762,"text":"Many of the subtasks in surgery are very\nroutine and tedious, like suturing,"},{"time":726555,"text":"and currently, all of these are performed"},{"time":728846,"text":"under the specific and immediate\ncontrol of the surgeon."},{"time":733374,"text":"So the surgeon becomes fatigued over time."},{"time":736086,"text":"And we've been wondering,"},{"time":737546,"text":"what if we could program the robot\nto perform some of these subtasks,"},{"time":741941,"text":"and thereby free the surgeon"},{"time":743346,"text":"to focus on the more complicated\nparts of the surgery,"},{"time":746605,"text":"and also cut down on the time\nthat the surgery would take"},{"time":749429,"text":"if we could get the robot\nto do them a little bit faster?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":752958,"text":"Now, it's hard to program a robot\nto do delicate things like this."},{"time":756943,"text":"But it turns out my colleague\nPieter Abbeel, who's here at Berkeley,"},{"time":761173,"text":"has developed a new set of techniques\nfor teaching robots from example."},{"time":767170,"text":"So he's gotten robots to fly helicopters,"},{"time":769937,"text":"do incredibly interesting,\nbeautiful acrobatics,"},{"time":773215,"text":"by watching human experts fly them."},{"time":776152,"text":"So we got one of these robots."},{"time":778082,"text":"We started working with Pieter\nand his students."},{"time":780646,"text":"And we asked a surgeon\nto perform a task --"},{"time":786761,"text":"with the robot."},{"time":787936,"text":"So what we're doing is asking\nthe surgeon to perform the task,"},{"time":790985,"text":"and we record the motions of the robot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793045,"text":"So here's an example."},{"time":794495,"text":"I'll use tracing out\na figure eight as an example."},{"time":798170,"text":"So here's what it looks like\nwhen the robot --"},{"time":801828,"text":"this is what the robot's path\nlooks like, those three examples."},{"time":804920,"text":"Now, those are much better\nthan what a novice like me could do,"},{"time":809080,"text":"but they're still jerky and imprecise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811798,"text":"So we record all these examples, the data,"},{"time":814763,"text":"and then go through a sequence of steps."},{"time":818278,"text":"First, we use a technique\ncalled dynamic time warping"},{"time":821428,"text":"from speech recognition."},{"time":822942,"text":"And this allows us to temporally\nalign all of the examples."},{"time":826918,"text":"And then we apply Kalman filtering,\na technique from control theory,"},{"time":832144,"text":"that allows us to statistically\nanalyze all the noise"},{"time":835137,"text":"and extract the desired\ntrajectory that underlies them."},{"time":841283,"text":"Now we take those human demonstrations --"},{"time":843857,"text":"they're all noisy and imperfect --"},{"time":845556,"text":"and we extract from them\nan inferred task trajectory"},{"time":848178,"text":"and control sequence for the robot."},{"time":851181,"text":"We then execute that on the robot,"},{"time":853521,"text":"we observe what happens,"},{"time":855570,"text":"then we adjust the controls,"},{"time":856951,"text":"using a sequence of techniques\ncalled iterative learning."},{"time":861129,"text":"Then what we do is we increase\nthe velocity a little bit."},{"time":865244,"text":"We observe the results,\nadjust the controls again,"},{"time":869340,"text":"and observe what happens."},{"time":871136,"text":"And we go through this several rounds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":873327,"text":"And here's the result."},{"time":874968,"text":"That's the inferred task trajectory,"},{"time":876730,"text":"and here's the robot\nmoving at the speed of the human."},{"time":879975,"text":"Here's four times the speed of the human."},{"time":882477,"text":"Here's seven times."},{"time":885004,"text":"And here's the robot operating\nat 10 times the speed of the human."},{"time":890762,"text":"So we're able to get a robot\nto perform a delicate task"},{"time":893687,"text":"like a surgical subtask,"},{"time":897081,"text":"at 10 times the speed of a human."},{"time":900185,"text":"So this project also,"},{"time":902469,"text":"because of its involved\npracticing and learning,"},{"time":905018,"text":"doing something over and over again,"},{"time":906804,"text":"this project also has a lesson, which is:"},{"time":909405,"text":"if you want to do something well,"},{"time":913084,"text":"there's no substitute\nfor practice, practice, practice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":921186,"text":"So these are four of the lessons\nthat I've learned from robots"},{"time":924697,"text":"over the years."},{"time":927312,"text":"And the field of robotics\nhas gotten much better over time."},{"time":934319,"text":"Nowadays, high school students\ncan build robots,"},{"time":936619,"text":"like the industrial robot\nmy dad and I tried to build."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940675,"text":"But, it's very -- now ..."},{"time":943954,"text":"And now, I have a daughter,"},{"time":947857,"text":"named Odessa."},{"time":949673,"text":"She's eight years old."},{"time":951682,"text":"And she likes robots, too."},{"time":953970,"text":"Maybe it runs in the family."}]},{"cues":[{"time":955390,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":956654,"text":"I wish she could meet my dad."},{"time":960303,"text":"And now I get to teach her\nhow things work,"},{"time":963067,"text":"and we get to build projects together."},{"time":965321,"text":"And I wonder what kind of lessons\nshe'll learn from them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":970147,"text":"Robots are the most human of our machines."},{"time":974983,"text":"They can't solve all\nof the world's problems,"},{"time":977961,"text":"but I think they have something\nimportant to teach us."},{"time":982276,"text":"I invite all of you"},{"time":984301,"text":"to think about the innovations\nthat you're interested in,"},{"time":988712,"text":"the machines that you wish for."},{"time":991660,"text":"And think about\nwhat they might be telling you."},{"time":995211,"text":"Because I have a hunch that many\nof our technological innovations,"},{"time":998980,"text":"the devices we dream about,"},{"time":1002166,"text":"can inspire us to be better humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005984,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007159,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}